      "notes": "Hand-seeded v1 priors. Mode is 'bounded_live' (graduated ladder): every active+applicable signal moves the prediction under hard single/family/plane caps, scaled by reliability_weight. The four high-confidence directional signals the engine has a validated prior for -- b2b_fatigue (transcribes the legacy _B2B_FATIGUE constants verbatim), rest_advantage, def_matchup_weak, def_matchup_strong -- carry reliability_weight=1.0 so they apply their capped prior in full. Every other coefficient has no fitted reliability_weight and so applies only the conservative 'unfitted_reliability_prior' (0.25 -> a sliver, not face value) until omega-fit-adjustment-policy measures it from CLV/direction history; fit-proved noise damps to weight~0 (a no-op). An operator may escalate to mode='live'. Set OMEGA_EVIDENCE_MODE=score_only to reproduce the legacy record-but-never-apply baseline.",
